ch.usi.dag.disl.staticcontext

Class InvocationStaticContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.usi.dag.disl.staticcontext.AbstractStaticContext
      • ch.usi.dag.disl.staticcontext.InvocationStaticContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StaticContext

    public class InvocationStaticContext
extends AbstractStaticContext
    Represents a static context for method invocations. Provides information related to a method invocation at a particular call site.

    Note: This context can only be used with the BytecodeMarker triggering on method invocation instructions, i.e., INVOKESTATIC, INVOKEVIRTUAL, INVOKESPECIAL, and INVOKEINTERFACE. If you are not sure whether the context can be used, use the isValid() method to check if the context is valid.

    Author:
    Aibek Sarimbekov, Lubomir Bulej
